  • Class
    Description
    AutoCommands
    The AutoCommands implements logic for each individual auto command.
    AutoSystem
    The AutoSystem implements all the logic to perform auto routines during competition.
    AutoSystem.Cmd
    Auto command enum.
    DriveSwerveSystem
    The SwerveDriveSystem is a pseudo static class that implements all functions necessary for a robot Swerve drive.

    The TankDriveSystem is a pseudo static class that implements all functions necessary for a robot tank drive.
    Lib4150AdvancedPID
    Advanced PID controller class.
    Lib4150DigitalCommand
    Implements a simple digital command.
    Lib4150DigitalDelay
    Digital time delay class.
    Lib4150DigitalEdgeChange
    The Lib4150DigitalEdgeChange class implements edge change detection, used by sequential boolean logic where the output is true only when the input changes from its previous state.
    Lib4150DigitalEdgeOff
    Lib4150DigitalEdgeOff class implements edge off detection, used by sequential boolean logic where the output is true only when the input transitions from true to false.
    Lib4150DigitalEdgeOn
    The DigEdgeOn class implements edge on detection, used by sequential boolean logic where the output is true only when the input transitions from false to true.
    Lib4150DigitalOffDelay
    Digital off delay class.
    Lib4150DigitalOnDelay
    Digital on delay class.
    Lib4150DigitalOneShot
    Digital one shot.
    Lib4150DigitalSetResetFlipFlop
    The SRFlipFlop class implements a set/reset flip flop, used in sequential digital logic.
    Lib4150ElapsedTime
    The Lib4150ElapsedTime class calculates the elapsed time from a particular starting point.
    Lib4150FilterLowPassBW1
    This class implements a 1st order low pass butterworth filter using finite differences.
    Lib4150JoystickArcadeCalc
    Calculate left and right wheel demands as a function of joystick used in arcade mode.
    Lib4150JoystickScale
    The Lib4150JoystickScale.jave class adds a deadband around 0 for the joystick.
    Lib4150MessageUtil
    Utility class to allow us to control what messages sent to the console are like.
